Notes: This column represents a unique identifier for each measurement, aligning with the 'hasMeasurementDateTime' path to relate measurement instances uniquely.
This column identifies the patient associated with the measurement, which matches the 'hasPatient' relationship in the ontology.
Measurement codes specify the type of measurement, which the 'hasCode' property directly relates to, making this path semantically appropriate.
The measurement value corresponds to a quantitative result, which aligns with the 'hasQuantity' property indicating a measurable quantity.
Measurement units are best represented using the 'hasCode' property, indicating the unit as a code from a controlled vocabulary.
This column contains date information for the measurement, directly corresponding to the 'hasDateTime' property with datatype dateTime.
